{
  "message": "test(fj-conformance): add smoke_harness_json fuzz target with 12 seeds\n\nIntroduce a new libFuzzer target, `smoke_harness_json`, that\nstress-tests the conformance crate's three JSON-backed loaders\nend-to-end against arbitrary fuzzer-supplied bytes. Previously\nthe conformance fuzz crate only exercised binary fixture decoders\n(raptorq, primitive_eval, value_deserializer, etc.) so the JSON\nparsing surface was effectively untouched by the fuzzer.\n\nLoaders exercised per fuzz iteration:\n\n- `read_fixture_note`: writes the input to a temp file, parses\n  it as a `FixtureNote`, and (when parsing succeeds) flips the\n  harness into both strict and hardened modes via\n  `HarnessConfig` and runs `run_smoke` against a temp oracle\n  root. This drives the note schema, the optional-fields\n  defaulting, and the strict/hardened branch of the smoke\n  pipeline from a single corpus.\n- `ParityCase` loader: lifts the bytes through `serde_json` into\n  `Vec<ParityCase>` and feeds them to `evaluate_parity`,\n  capping at `MAX_PARITY_CASES` (64) so pathological inputs\n  can't OOM the fuzzer worker.\n- `ParityReport` loader: round-trips the bytes through the\n  report deserializer, covering the read path that downstream\n  CI consumes.\n\nGuard rails: inputs over 16 KiB are rejected up-front, and every\nfilesystem operation (`tempdir`, `write`, `create_dir_all`) is\nlet-Ok-else-return so a transient temp-fs failure aborts the\niteration instead of panicking the harness.\n\nCargo.toml: register `smoke_harness_json` as a `[[bin]]` entry\nalongside the existing fuzz targets, with `test/doc/bench` set\nto `false` to match the rest of the fuzz crate.\n\nCorpus seeds (12 total) split by loader:\n\n- fixture_note loader: `fixture_note_minimal`,\n  `fixture_note_empty_strings`, `fixture_note_extra_fields`,\n  `fixture_note_long_unicode`, `fixture_note_missing_notes`.\n- parity case loader: `parity_cases_empty`,\n  `parity_cases_all_match`, `parity_cases_mixed`,\n  `parity_cases_empty_fields`.\n- parity report loader: `parity_report_consistent`,\n  `parity_report_inconsistent`.\n- shared malformed seed: `malformed_truncated` for the\n  early-EOF / unterminated-JSON branches.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
